engineDB::query()

Description
    public mixed engineDB::query(string $query)
    Performs a MySQL query.

Parameters
    query
    A string value containing a valid MySQL query.

Return Values
    Returns FALSE on failure; ID on insert; TRUE on UPDATE, DELETE, DROP; and resource on SELECT, SHOW, DESCRIBE, EXPLAIN and other statements returning 
    resultset.
    If $this->queryArray == TRUE an array is returned with the following structure
	$array['result'] = The contents returned if arrayReturn == FALSE
	$array['affectedRows']
	$array['errorNumber'] = FALSE unless defined
	$array['error'] = FALSE unless defined
	$array['info'] = The results of mysql_info()
	$array['id'] = ID of the last insert if the previous query was INSERT; otherwise FALSE
	$array['query'] = The query which was sent

Examples
    <?php
	...
	$query = sprintf("select * from log where date > %s and date < %s",
	    $engineDB->escape($this->startTime),
	    $engineDB->escape($this->endTime));
	
	$this->sanitize = FALSE;
	$results        = $engineDB->query($query);
        ...
    ?>
Notes
    $this->sanitize is reset to TRUE after executing.
